rtes |sopt=t}}\n* {{Librivox author | id=4158}}\n* [http://www-groups.dcs.st-and.ac.uk/~history/Mathematicians/Descartes.html Detailed biography of Descartes at MacTutor]\n* {{Cite CE1913|wstitle=Ren\u00e9 Descartes}}\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20081220142538/http://www.freewebs.com/dqsdnlj/d.html John Cottingham translation of ''Meditations'' and ''Objections and Replies''.]\n* [http://digitalcommons.unl.edu/modlangfrench/20/ Ren\u00e9 Descartes (1596\u20131650)] Published in ''Encyclopedia of Rhetoric and Composition'' (1996)\n* [http://www.earlymoderntexts.com A site containing Descartes' main works, including correspondence, slightly modified for easier reading]\n* [https://archive.org/details/descartesphiloso010838mbp Descartes Philosophical Writings tr. by Norman Kemp Smith] at archive.org\n* [https://archive.org/details/studiesincartes00smitgoog Studies in the Cartesian philosophy (1902) by Norman Kemp Smith] at archive.org\n* [https://archive.org/details/philosophicalwor005524mbp The Philosophical Works Of Descartes Volume II (1934)] at archive.org\n* [http://www-personal.umich.edu/~jbourj/money5.htm Descartes featured on the 100 French Franc banknote from 1942.]\n* {{IMSLP|id=Descartes, Ren\u00e9}}\n* {{MathGenealogy|id=125358}}\n* [http://www.cartesius.net Centro Interdipartimentale di Studi su Descartes e il Seicento]\n* Livre Premier, ''La G\u00e9om\u00e9trie'', online and analyzed by A. Warusfel, [http://www.bibnum.education.fr/mathematiques/geometrie/le-livre-premier-de-la-geometrie-de-descartes ''BibNum'']<small>[click \"\u00e0 t\u00e9l\u00e9charger\" for English analysis]</small>\n\n===Bibliographies===\n* [https://archive.is/20160110112345/http://www.cartesius.net/menu-demo/bibliografia-cartesiana ''Bibliografia cartesiana/Bibliographie cart\u00e9sienne on-line (1997\u20132012)'']\n\n===''Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy''===\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/descartes/ Descartes]\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/descartes-works/ Life and works]\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/descartes-epistemology/ Epistemology]\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/descartes-mathematics/ Mathematics]\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/descartes-physics/ Physics]\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/descartes-ethics/ Ethics]\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/descartes-modal/ Modal Metaphysics]\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/descartes-ontological/ Ontological Argument]\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/descartes-ideas/ Theory of Ideas]\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/pineal-gland/ Pineal Gland]\n* [http://plato.stanford.edu/entries/descartes-works/history.html Law Thesis]\n\n===''Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy''===\n* [http://www.iep.utm.edu/descarte/ Descartes]\n* [http://www.iep.utm.edu/desc-sci/ Scientific Method]\n* [http://www.iep.utm.edu/descmind/ Mind-Body Distinction]\n\n===Other===\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=44h9QuWcJYk ''Bernard Williams interviewed about Descartes on \"Men of ideas\"'']\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Articles related to Ren\u00e9 Descartes\n|list =\n{{Age of Enlightenment}}\n{{Metaphysics}}\n{{Epistemology}}\n{{Philosophy of mind}}\n{{Philosophy of science}}\n{{Philosophy of religion}}\n{{Consciousness}}\n{{Catholic philosophy footer}}\n{{History of Catholic theology}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Descartes, Rene}}\n[[Category:Ren\u00e9 Descartes| ]]\n[[Category:Cartesianism|*]]\n[[Category:1596 births]]\n[[Category:1650 deaths]]\n[[Category:17th-century Dutch philosophers]]\n[[Category:17th-century Dutch scientists]]\n[[Category:17th-century French mathematicians]]\n[[Category:17th-century French philosophers]]\n[[Category:17th-century French scientists]]\n[[Category:17th-century French writers]]\n[[Category:17th-century Latin-language writers]]\n[[Category:17th-century male writers]]\n[[Category:17th-century mathematicians]]\n[[Category:17th-century philosophers]]\n[[Category:Age of Enlightenment]]\n[[Category:Aphorists]]\n[[Ca