{"title_page": "List of glam metal bands and artists", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}\nThe following is a '''list of glam metal bands and artists''' and includes bands and artists that have been described as [[glam metal]] or its interchangeable terms, hair metal,{{sfn|Weinstein|2015|pp=223\u201326}}<ref name=\"Ramirez\">{{cite web|first= Carlos |last= Ramirez |title= Top 10 Musicians with Hair Metal Pasts |publisher= [[Noisecreep]] |url= http://noisecreep.com/top-10-musicians-with-hair-metal-pasts/ |accessdate= 18 April 2010}}</ref> hair bands,{{sfn|Witmer|2010|p=22}} pop metal{{sfn|Weinstein|2015|pp=223\u201326}} and lite metal{{sfn|Weinstein|2015|pp=223\u201326}} by professional journalists at some stage in their career. Glam metal is a [[subgenre]] of [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]]<ref>{{cite news|first= Jane |last= Stevenson |title= 'Headbanger' is Heavy Metal: 101 |newspaper= [[Toronto Sun]] |publisher= [[Jam!]] |date= 24 February 2006 |accessdate= 16 July 2016 |url= http://jam.canoe.com/Movies/Reviews/M/Metal_A_Headbangers_Journey/2006/02/24/1460060.html}}</ref> and is influenced by 1970s [[glam rock]].<ref>{{cite web|first= Chad |last= Bowar |title= What Is Hair Metal? |date= 17 February 2016 |publisher= [[About.com]] |url= http://heavymetal.about.com/od/heavymetal101/p/hairmetal.htm |accessdate= 16 July 2016}}</ref> Glam metal groups wear \"... flashy clothing, heavy makeup, and large, teased hair ...\".<ref>{{cite web|title= Pop/Rock \u00bb Heavy Metal \u00bb Hair Metal |publisher= [[AllMusic]] |url= http://www.allmusic.com/style/hair-metal-ma0000011902 |accessdate= 16 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n{|border=\"0\" align=\"center\" class=\"toccolours\"\n!{{MediaWiki:Toc}}\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|'''[[#Glam metal bands and artists|Glam metal bands and artists]]''': [[#A|A]] [[#B|B]] [[#C|C]] [[#D|D]] [[#E|E]] [[#F|F]] [[#G|G]] [[#H|H]] [[#I|I]] [[#J|J]] [[#K|K]] [[#L|L]] [[#M|M]] [[#N|N]] [[#O|O]] [[#P|P]] [[#Q|Q]] [[#R|R]] [[#S|S]] [[#T|T]] [[#U|