|pp=223\u201326}} by professional journalists at some stage in their career. Glam metal is a [[subgenre]] of [[heavy metal music|heavy metal]]<ref>{{cite news|first= Jane |last= Stevenson |title= 'Headbanger' is Heavy Metal: 101 |newspaper= [[Toronto Sun]] |publisher= [[Jam!]] |date= 24 February 2006 |accessdate= 16 July 2016 |url= http://jam.canoe.com/Movies/Reviews/M/Metal_A_Headbangers_Journey/2006/02/24/1460060.html}}</ref> and is influenced by 1970s [[glam rock]].<ref>{{cite web|first= Chad |last= Bowar |title= What Is Hair Metal? |date= 17 February 2016 |publisher= [[About.com]] |url= http://heavymetal.about.com/od/heavymetal101/p/hairmetal.htm |accessdate= 16 July 2016}}</ref> Glam metal groups wear \"... flashy clothing, heavy makeup, and large, teased hair ...\".<ref>{{cite web|title= Pop/Rock \u00bb Heavy Metal \u00bb Hair Metal |publisher= [[AllMusic]] |url= http://www.allmusic.com/style/hair-metal-ma0000011902 |accessdate= 16 July 2016}}</ref>\n\n{|border=\"0\" align=\"center\" class=\"toccolours\"\n!{{MediaWiki:Toc}}\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|'''[[#Glam metal bands and artists|Glam metal bands and artists]]''': [[#A|A]] [[#B|B]] [[#C|C]] [[#D|D]] [[#E|E]] [[#F|F]] [[#G|G]] [[#H|H]] [[#I|I]] [[#J|J]] [[#K|K]] [[#L|L]] [[#M|M]] [[#N|N]] [[#O|O]] [[#P|P]] [[#Q|Q]] [[#R|R]] [[#S|S]] [[#T|T]] [[#U|U]] [[#V|V]] [[#W|W]] [[#X|X]] [[#Y|Y]] [[#Z|Z]]<br/>'''[[#Glam metal revival bands|Glam metal revival bands]]'''\n__NOTOC__\n|}\n\n==Glam metal bands and artists==\n<!--All unsourced additions will be removed. Please provide sources for any additions-->\n\n===A===\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*[[Accept (band)|Accept]] (''[[Eat the Heat]]'' era){{sfn|Popoff|2014|p=170}}\n*[[Aerosmith]]{{sfn|Harrington|2002|p=392}}<ref name=\"Pop Metal\"/>\n*[[Alias (band)|Alias]]<ref>{{cite web|title= The 10 best Canadian one-hit wonders of the '90s |date= 26 February 2015 |publisher= [[CBC Music]] |url= http://beta.cbcmusic.ca/posts/11316/the-10-best-canadian-one-hit-wonders-of-the-90