ood, Sweat & Towers'' |date= 6 July 2006 |work= [[Pitchfork Media]] |url= http://pitchfork.com/reviews/albums/9140-blood-sweat-towers/ |accessdate= 16 July 2016}}</ref>\n*[[We Are Harlot]]<ref name=\"Revival\"/>\n{{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of heavy metal bands]]\n*[[List of glam rock artists]]\n{{clear}}\n\n==Notes==\n{{reflist|25em}}\n\n==References==\n{{div col|colwidth=30em}}\n*{{cite book|first=Ian|last=Christe|authorlink=Ian Christe|title=Sound of the Beast: The Complete Headbanging History of Heavy Metal|year=2003|publisher=[[HarperCollins]]|isbn=978-0-380-81127-4|ref=harv|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/soundofbeastcomp0000chri}}\n*{{cite book|first=Brian|last=Cogan|title=Cult Pop Culture: How the Fringe Became Mainstream|year=2011|chapter=What Died in the 1980s Should Stay Dead: The Repeated Rebirth of Hair Bands|publisher=[[ABC-CLIO]]|pages=161\u201369|editor-first=Bob|editor-last=Batchelor|isbn=978-0-313-35780-0|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|first=Brian|last=Giffin|title=Encyclopaedia of Australian Heavy Metal|year=2015|edition=3rd|publisher=Dark Star|url= https://books.google.com/books?id=QK3JCQAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover|isbn=978-0-9943206-1-2|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|first=Joe S.|last=Harrington|title=Sonic Cool: The Life & Death of Rock 'n' Roll|year=2002|publisher=[[Hal Leonard Corporation]]|isbn=0-634-02861-8|ref=harv|url=https://archive.org/details/soniccoollifedea00harr}}\n*{{cite book|first=Brad|last=Klypchak|chapter=All Those Wasted Years: Hanoi Rocks and the Transitions of Glam|title=Global Glam and Popular Music: Style and Spectacle from the 1970s to the 2000s|year=2016|editor-first1=Ian|editor-last1=Chapman|editor-first2=Henry|editor-last2=Johnson|pages=142\u201355|publisher=Routledge|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|first=Joel|last=McIver|authorlink=Joel McIver|title=Nu Metal: The Next Generation of Rock & Punk|year=2002|publisher=Omnibus Press|isbn=978-0-7119-9209-2|ref=harv}}\n*{{cite book|first=Marcus|last=Moberg|ti